* Kyoto Betsuin
* {{ill|Nagoya Betsuin|ja|專修寺名古屋別院|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagoya Betsuin|qq=}}
* Kobe Betsuin
* Hokkaido Betsuin (Kiyota-ku, Sapporo, Hokkaido)
* Fukui Betsuin
* Kanto Betsuin
* Yokohama Betsuin

== Characteristics ==
Takada-ha uniquely uses ''Bunrui-ge'' ({{ill|Hymns of the Pure Land|ja|文類慰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hymns of the Pure Land|qq=}}) for evening services, unlike other Jōdo Shinshū sects that primarily recite ''Shōshin-ge'' ({{ill|Hymns of True Faith|ja|正信慰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hymns of True Faith|qq=}}). Additionally, its temples traditionally do not use {{ill|Tannishō|ja|商異止|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tannishō|qq=}}, as the sect preserves a large collection of Shinran's original writings.

