== Characteristics == Takada-ha uniquely uses ''Bunrui-ge'' ({{ill|Hymns of the Pure Land|ja|文類慰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hymns of the Pure Land|qq=}}) for evening services, unlike other Jōdo Shinshū sects that primarily recite ''Shōshin-ge'' ({{ill|Hymns of True Faith|ja|正信慰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hymns of True Faith|qq=}}). Additionally, its temples traditionally do not use {{ill|Tannishō|ja|商異止|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tannishō|qq=}}, as the sect preserves a large collection of Shinran's original writings.
